document.title: 2023 Oregon Health Standards K-12 Health Education Adopted October 19, 2023

6906F6C6AD594A1A8375753F1C11F45C.description:
Analyze systemic barriers to sexual, reproductive, and obstetric care, including
prenatal care, childbirth, and postpartum care.

DF7E7A767F494968BB5101CBEB1AF6E8.description:
Analyze how history can influence attitudes, beliefs, and expectations about sexuality
and identity, including the history of medical experimentation and eugenics.

14BE13DAD44B4F7EBC90F5BB789BC1E4.description:
Define reproductive justice and explain its history and how it relates to sexual health
and health equity.

78F937B9F64446A99B0CCC2A7383ACDE.description:
Analyze public health and government policies on sexual and reproductive health
practices.

EEE5B08C5646429B86E9EDCB628C2044.description:
Describe body literacy skills to notice changes, pain, including menstrual pain, or
discomfort in one’s body related to the sexual and reproductive system and identify
when to seek support from trusted adults and medical professionals.

D680A780BBF24A6D925CFF0A222A5194.description:
Assess the validity, reliability, and accessibility of comprehensive sexual and
reproductive health information, products, and services offered online and in the
local community.

E2CA30C969044361A0688DA039D0C853.description:
Discuss responsibilities around sexually transmitted infection (STI) prevention,
testing, treatment, and disclosure to sexual partners.

BAB6A8A630AA4A7FA1AE28DE81306729.description:
Analyze political and historical issues that were rooted in and have resulted in
discrimination, oppression, and stigma against historically and currently marginalized
people, including those with sexually transmitted infections (STIs) and HIV/AIDS.

A9991FC1FBF74AB38795FB389990199A.description:
Identify medically accurate sources of information for pregnancy, prenatal care, and
pregnancy options, including parenting, surrogacy, adoption, abortion, and safe
surrender, including community resources.

D8F619B84CAE4A23A457A4557CAE884F.description:
Practice demonstrating the correct usage of barrier methods including external and
internal condoms and dental dams.

D833ED4FAF8C46439EEDC7C2BD1781C7.description:
Compare and contrast methods to prevent unintended pregnancy, considering
effectiveness, access, and personal impact on health.

A17473BF10704F42921CB6934B2FEF12.description:
Identify individual, familial, cultural, and systemic influences on barrier methods and
contraceptive use.

AE5D75052AA3434B9143C79C241D1E17.description: Discuss skills and resources that can support people navigating parenthood.

FB15E97F26234433A482787E579928B4.description: Summarize fertilization, fetal development, and childbirth.

A4381EFE9C9C4BDE98B5B4684CF5EEBB.description:
Describe how to make a decision about sexual behaviors, including virtual and inperson, that takes into consideration personal values and health and safety of self
and others.

E4059CFE7C394038B5FF7C95DD553789.description:
Demonstrate the ability to effectively communicate with a partner to make decisions
around abstinence and consensual sexual intimacy.

30AE55E7C7BC4387A1BA0396A556B647.description:
Analyze societal factors that might inhibit honest discussion between sexual and
romantic partners about their sexual histories, including sexually transmitted
infections (STIs) and HIV/AIDS status, and identify ways to begin open and honest
conversations.

94143486D02B4C8E929B0FC1DC9CF8A4.description:
Analyze familial factors that can limit access to genetic health information for many
people, including adoption, foster care, migration, and donor conception.

0A479E29F39B46F9AB69ECED46509B84.description:
Analyze how peers, media, family, society, culture, and a person's intersecting
identities can influence attitudes, beliefs, and expectations about sexual and
romantic orientation.

1F42A97316E24A33BE894FB8600CA189.description:
Explain how identity-affirming support from peers, families, schools, communities
and health care providers can improve a person's health and well-being.

22EB827662E348A4B8EB082105C6D82D.description:
Analyze the impact of Oregon’s Menstrual Dignity Act on menstruation stigma and
period poverty.

DF27EF7A010A48D1A298FEBB8DB42322.description:
Describe the cognitive, social, and emotional changes of adolescence and throughout
adulthood.

423C0A909BD04DD3801B482A3E21BD9C.description:
Explain the human reproductive and sexual response systems, including
differentiating between internal and external body parts and their functions, and that
there are variations in human bodies, including different shapes of vulvas,
circumcised and uncircumcised penises, and intersex conditions.

8760D7682013486E973A9450AC0AC176.description:
Analyze how peers, media, family, society, history, culture, and a person's
intersecting identities can influence self-concept, body image, and self-esteem.

EDC8A7980B66472DA1DBE3A036946851.description:
Summarize individual rights and responsibilities in regards to sexual consent, sexually
explicit media, and sexting under state and federal law.

4CB5542F35424F18AA8408155DE547FA.description: Explain trafficking, including tactics people use to traffic and exploit youth.

1B4F28102136455CAD12D824752F3C1B.description:
Explain why a person who has been sexually harassed, abused, assaulted, or is a
survivor/victim of child sexual abuse, rape, domestic violence, dating violence, or sex
trafficking, is never to blame for the action of the perpetrator.

F4BBF990C59540BB8A5C8BE2530C43E3.description:
Describe the types of abuse, including physical, emotional, psychological, financial,
and sexual, and the cycle of violence as it relates to sexual abuse, domestic violence,
dating violence, trafficking, and gender-based violence.

BF8C87328937499FB80741EB67D77154.description:
Model how to be an upstander by addressing hurtful comments, addressing concepts
of intent, impact, and repair.

A38C8080F4D04AD08C5045C2E0C9D3DB.description:
Explain the impact media, including sexually explicit media, social media, and artificial
intelligence (AI) can have on one's perceptions of, and expectations for, a healthy
relationship.

EB853956ED0240CBBB27DBE57CF7DE8E.description:
Demonstrate ways to support a fellow student who is being sexually harassed or
abused.

640047E024074D469A8E8FC5BBFC2582.description:
Describe how to access resources for survivors of interpersonal violence, sexual
violence and sex trafficking, including local confidential advocacy resources.

3C6FF2EB021C4C6F850848A1303550FC.description:
Apply a decision-making model to maintaining a healthy relationship and ending an
unhealthy relationship.

E320AD43F9E94151A7346BDA4186F667.description:
Examine the impact of power differences within relationships and other factors that
can affect the ability to give or perceive consent, including in sexual activity.

CF3EE62579E24212A5A5DDA89227F50A.description:
Analyze how culture and society can perpetuate stereotypes and expectations of
people with different genders in relationships.

54168C80FFDC4550B12449A52CC4B3A6.description:
Analyze different ways that people can express consensual physical affection, love,
friendship, empathy, and sympathy within different types of relationships.

3422EF049DA1453B84B722EED46C99C7.description:
TSEL Practices 2A Manage and express thoughts, emotions, impulses, and stressors ways
that affirm one’s identity.

6B472D42D02C42F2827FDD7918924216.description: Analyze laws related to minors accessing mental health care.

31FAE5F8CF074D458496D7BFB2F809FA.description:
Advocate for safer school communities to prevent bullying and violence and improve
mental health.

A55C70AA7F2D41C19379610034B3F7FC.description:
Analyze the impact of media, marketing, social media, internet use, and other
technologies on social, mental, and emotional health.

38483235B6854391B64246184AA4BDFA.description:
Describe the signs and symptoms of mental health challenges, including the warning
signs of suicide, self-harm, eating disorders and disordered eating, and other unsafe
behaviors.

E9B5061AE1EF400094C35543FB487ECC.description:
Compare the validity, reliability, and accessibility of mental, social, and emotional
health information, products, and services in the home, at school, and in the
community.

185189F09FA8472B884FC11A3AF9A9EB.description: Identify activities that promote social, emotional, and mental health.

CC083AEED909478E9336F116F2027BEB.description:
Analyze physical and psychological effects of stress, anxiety, depression, social
isolation, and individual and collective trauma.

F82D93B376A746F2BEB1CD447C643BF9.description:
TSEL Practice 5A Demonstrate curiosity and open-mindedness while using critical
thinking skills across various situations and environments.

EFD26518B3684C51975B1363A8EB5C60.description:
TSEL Practices 2C Plan, evaluate, and achieve personal and collective goals and
aspirations.

60F0D7A8761142B088E0FB03D9E34948.description:
Identify policies, practices, and resources that support access to nutritious food,
clean water, and accessible places for physical activity.

A43B6FA764EE47DD90C405F137573F66.description: Describe how to prevent foodborne illnesses.

BE961B8E88BD438398B9BC781CCC5443.description:
Analyze the influences of family, peers, school, community, culture, and social norms
on personal values and beliefs about food choices and physical activity.

058AE28182F84F08B895ADF5F9B19851.description:
Analyze how people from all cultures and backgrounds are connected by their use of
and shared experiences around food.

0C85F25AF493403293727F2F7651DC71.description: Describe how to make nutritious food and beverage choices at home, school, and when dining out.

FB136092E1054D47851A7C233F6D9AAC.description:
Create a personal short- and long-term goal that incorporates nutritious eating,
hydration, and physical activity as a daily part of life based on personal, cultural, and
community influences.

A45194FF2D274FD1B77D06A5657FDF93.description:
Explain the importance of drinking water and limiting sugar sweetened beverages
and its effect on health.

0BBA97C4D22E45FB9BD4C95FFA0A34FF.description:
Evaluate the physical, emotional, and mental impacts of missing or skipping meals
and “fad” dieting.

9D9A14A7A13E44E8B6598135D8B88EEB.description: Plan or prepare a balanced meal with nutrient-rich basic ingredients.

FEE2B02E969A4DA0B4CEEA925F645B05.description:
Analyze the political, economic, social, and environmental factors that influence our
current food system.

AD0212ED7F1B4E40860D96EEBE6EA62B.description:
Analyze the influence of public health and government laws and policies, as well as
media and marketing, on alcohol, marijuana/cannabis, tobacco, and other drugs, past
and present.

CD1437F06B9844358A13EB172EF6AC15.description:
Access and analyze the validity of information related to alcohol, marijuana/cannabis,
tobacco, and other drug use, misuse, and abuse prevention.

736A024066984F5880D59EA89EFD33FE.description:
Describe how to access support services needed for substance misuse and abuse,
harm reduction services, including needle exchanges, test strips, and prescription
disposal sites, and community resources to help someone stop using.

DD1AFC632CC44820B7E3A720F8337841.description:
Evaluate communication skills to manage social pressure to avoid or reduce health
risks around substance use.

3D35A27E54C3408399DB19875027BF9A.description:
Demonstrate decision-making skills in regards to substance use, misuse, and abuse in
varying situations.

5B37597ED9394BD696D1059CC06C9D6E.description:
Identify potential barriers to making healthy decisions regarding substance use and
identify personal strategies and community support to overcome those barriers.

72ADF47F35874160903BBE035D95E980.description:
Analyze reasons why individuals use or do not use alcohol, marijuana/cannabis,
tobacco, and other drugs, including the influence of family, peers, school,
community, culture, and social norms on personal values, beliefs, and behaviors.

C03FF239C0D1490AAD436CABB5694AE3.description:
Analyze the relationship between substance use, misuse, abuse and other health
risks, including unintentional injuries, violence, self-harm, suicide, and sexual risk
behaviors.

399CDAB72CE64F4EA4B13D078198AF0B.description:
Analyze the data on overdose and fentanyl laced over-the-counter and prescription
medications.

7FF73B67074C4899BDC9123230E59007.description:
Analyze how laws, rules, policies, and regulations influence health promotion and
disease prevention related to tobacco, marijuana, and other drugs.

80D1EAD63D024BDAB5F2920E5C2C0AC3.description:
Access valid and reliable health information on short- and long-term effects of
substance use from print and electronic materials that are available from credible
health organizations.

3519F0647C2E4A029D78EE4103BE921C.description:
Identify how to recognize and respond to overdose emergencies, including how to
access, administer, and use naloxone for opioid overdose prevention and reversal.

0266A40FA3CA4E65AB1383F2010BC287.description:
Identify and promote protective factors related to substance use, misuse, and abuse,
including harm reduction and emergency action.

0A8462AC6AF242E79EA5103F2F207EF2.description: Evaluate strategies for using social media safely, legally, and respectfully.

ECF86872D6CF45FBA3F2D31AEDD71A0C.description:
Analyze community and individual preparation and emergency response in case of
natural disasters, including wildfires and earthquakes, and acts of violence.

196A7DB6A4D6415CA59FF4F3F7E59A72.description:
Examine laws and practices related to increasing accessibility for people with
disabilities and identify why they are important for individual, interpersonal,
community, and environmental health.

3C24877CDA67442182C59F7583BCCABB.description:
Access a variety of resources in the home, school, and community that prevent
injury.

544CFE8DDE8C4A36A39EB6515633E195.description:
Demonstrate how to administer basic first aid, hands-only cardiopulmonary
resuscitation (CPR), use of an automated external defibrillator (AED), and treatment
of an opioid overdose emergency.

B4AFFEEACB57454583527A4F800CA9C6.description:
Formulate a plan to recognize and respond to situations that may lead to injury
between individuals, in groups, and in communities.

EA387C5B061B4A719760FD77E53F058E.description: Analyze current data on unintentional injury among adolescents.

D3672FAE22344A4CBB0375E7268B0010.description:
Advocate for everyone, regardless of physical ability or location, to have access to
nutritious food, clean water, clean air, and accessible places.

8205C183A9454DB9B4761C39AEA2BB9F.description:
Discuss the intersections between built environment, green spaces, climate change,
and the five dimensions of health.

02E047610EF546AC8715A13AD6ADE0FB.description:
Analyze how the history of health and social policy impacts individual and community
health status.

A8183FDA270640B6A862B2B28703FD70.description:
Analyze how public health policies and government regulations can influence health
promotion and disease prevention.

648E87EFDB72459192C519B3B13990CE.description: Demonstrate how to access medically accurate, comprehensive, and inclusive healthrelated resources online and in the community or at school.

F9F401F2165D489AA0F67005A3780C43.description:
Identify and discuss the life-saving benefits of organ and tissue donation, and analyze
how personal, familial, media, and cultural factors influence decisions about
donation.

54F1248D30A146A58044DEE3475E78A7.description:
Identify at least two strategies to promote health and wellness for individuals,
families, and communities.

44CB57CD9B8844239E85B048F11AC15E.description: Identify individual practices that protect vision, hearing, skin, and teeth.

A4E28B522CA84BD4863103A2194C1FE2.description:
Analyze health promotion and disease prevention guidelines and recommendations,
including those for infectious diseases, from credible federal, professional, and
voluntary health organizations.

1A667B3A3C0C44F9A8EC76D9AFFBE376.description:
Discuss personal and family values and behaviors that impact individual,
interpersonal, and community health.

00E946934A6449FC8AC0125CFEBC403E.description:
Identify and describe personal activities and behaviors within the five dimensions of
health (physical, social, emotional, mental, and environmental) and how they affect
health-related behaviors and impact holistic well-being.
